\section*{FUNCTIONS OF THE HEALTH RECORDS AND INFORMATION DEPARTMENT}

By the end of the session, participants should be able to:-
i. Identify the main function of Health Records and Information Department
ii. Relationship between Health Records Department and other Departments

\section*{1. Reception}

This is the area where patients/clients are welcomed and sorted and directed els ewhere for treatment or other services

\section*{2. Registration}

This is the recording of identification and social details of the patient/ client i.e. name, address, sex, residence and other identification information

\section*{3. Admission}

This is the procedure carried out when the patient is required to be confirmed to a hospital ward/bed for further treatment or service

\section*{4. Discharge}

This is the procedure that is carried out when the patient has undergone treatment or consumed
services and has been allowed to return to their home/ residence

\section*{5. Appointment}

This is the procedure that allows for the patient/ client who has been ordered by the attending doctor/ clinician to return to the hospital at a future date for treatment

\section*{6. Filing}

This is a systematic way of keeping individual health care document and aggregate documents in
appropriate equipment and using appropriate methods

\section*{7. Tracing}

This is the control of the movement of patient/ client records or documents

\section*{8. Clinic preparation}

This is the getting ready all patient/clients documents at least two days before the client/patient
returns to hospital for treatment or other service

\section*{9. Follow up}

This is a mechanism put in place so that patients/client diagnosed with certain diseases/conditions usually long term, or infectious and who have been discharged are treated away from the hospital, either at their homes or nearby hospitals to ensure the disease/condition is monitored

\section*{10. Coding and indexing}

This is the allocation of symbols/numbers that are predetermined for each condition to the disease that the patient/ client is suffering from: This code is then recorded together with all similar dis ease hence indexing. Collection tabulation, analysis, interpretation and dissemination of health care data. Data on individual patients and on segment of/or the who, population is gathered processed, made meaningful and given to those who need the information

