Tuberculosis, maternity, genitor-urinary, HIV/AIDS, assault etc. information is us ually given special attention

\section*{13. Design medical forms and computer views (E.g. DHIS)}

The Health Records and Information department is expected to ensure capturing of information is neat, accurate, and consistent. This is achieved by capturing the data uniformly in standard forms and in consultation with the users.

\section*{14. Ensuring quality assurance}

The Health Records Information Department ens ures that the highest standards of information capture, use, maintenance/storage and disposal are established and maintained

