Note: This check for accuracy means that patients who no longer need admission are not sent for and that the waiting list statistics are not wrongly inflated. It also reassures patient that the hospital has not forgotten about them.

\section*{c) Checking for duplication}
-The admission forms of routine and emergency admission should be checked against alphabetical file. In this way the card of a patient who has been in the routine waiting list for the repair of hernia will be removed. If this patient is admitted as an emergency with a strangulated hernia. Similarly if a patient is admitted with bronchitis and his name is on the waiting list for removal of tonsils the card relating to the tonsils should be marked admitted with bronchitis and date so that it cannot be sent for to come to the hospital for the operation when it is already an inpatient in the hospital.

